Martin Campbell-Kelly FCBS FLSW is an Emeritus Professor at the University of Warwick who has specialised in the history of computing.Campbell-Kelly has served on the editorial board of the IEEE Annals of the History of Computing journal. He is a committee member of the Computer Conservation Society, a Specialist Group of the British Computer Society, and is a Gresham College lecturer.In 2011, Campbell-Kelly was elected a Fellow of the Learned Society of Wales.

Education
Campell-Kelly was educated at Sunderland Polytechnic where he was awarded a PhD in 1980 on the Foundations of computer programming in Britain 1945â€“1955.

Research
Campbell-Kelly has authored, edited numerous books and journal articles on the history of computing.

